CREATE TABLE songs (id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR(255), duration INT, album_id INT, FOREIGN KEY(album_id) REFERENCES albums(id))</t><stat>SELECT artists.name, AVG(songs.duration) AS avg_duration FROM artists JOIN albums ON artists.id = albums.artist_id JOIN songs ON albums.id = songs.album_id GROUP BY artists.name</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), genre VARCHAR(255))

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL

CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>SELECT * FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>SELECT * FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>SELECT * FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>SELECT artist_name FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><stat>SELECT artist_id, artist_name FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>SELECT artist_id, artist_name FROM artists</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)

);

    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,

);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    song_id INT,

);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,

);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,

    artist_id INT,

);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)

    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>select * from song_genre</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE songs (

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>SELECT s.song_name, a.album_name FROM songs s JOIN albums a ON s.album_id = a.album_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

);

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><stat>select s.song_name, a.album_name from songs s join albums a on s.album_id = a.album_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE genres (

    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><stat>select s.song_name, g.genre_name from songs s join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),

);

);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>select s.song_name, g.genre_name from songs s join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>SELECT s.song_name, g.genre_name FROM songs s JOIN song_genre sg ON s.song_id = sg.song_id JOIN genres g ON sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)

    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><stat>select a.artist_name, g.genre_name from artists a join albums al on a.artist_id = al.artist_id join songs s on al.album_id = s.album_id join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

</t><stat>select a.artist_name, g.genre_name from artists a join albums al on a.artist_id = al.artist_id join songs s on al.album_id = s.album_id join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</stat>
